@NODE install "Installation & Configuration"
@{u}Installation & Configuration@{uu}

   Firstly, unarchive or copy these files to @{b}Doors:@{ub}, so everything resides in
@{b}Doors:DownTown/@{ub}. You're ready to rock!

Install it on every download function in your menus, for example:

Key   Function    Extra    Lo acc   Hi acc   Filename/Name/Dest/Path
D     24          20       5        10000    

Would become...

Key   Function    Extra    Lo acc   Hi acc   Filename/Name/Dest/Path
D     34          20        5        10000    Doors:DownTown/DT

(The extra column has no effect, change it to `0' if you like)

To download specific files:

Key   Function    Extra    Lo acc   Hi acc   Filename/Name/Dest/Path
D     34          0        5        10000    Doors:DownTown/DT [FILENAME]

[FILENAME] is the full path & filename of the file you wish to send.

Note: If you can't be bothered to enter Doors:DownTown/DT for every download
option you could:

Assign DT: to Doors:DownTown/

That way all you need to do then is enter:

DT:DT

for every download function.

   If you use ISO instead of IBM characters, you may want to check out the
files ending in @{b}.ISO@{ub} as these are ISO versions of the ANSI files,
simply copy them over the top of the relevant @{b}.text@{ub} files to use these
instead.

   There is no configuration file, and FILENAME is the only option, so you
can't go wrong really...  Can you? (Awaits the e-mails ;)...)

@{u}ANSI Screens@{uu}

   There are 3 ANSI screens used by DownTown, these are included in the archive
(direct from MagicFile!). Edit this to whatever you like but keep the
positioning the same and the @{b}Ratio.text@{ub} should not have a screen clear
in!

@ENDNODE


@NODE use "In use"
@{u}Usage@{uu}

   The user selects files as normal and when Download is selected it runs
DownTown instead, this will display a gauge showing current ratio statistics
and some more info and ask the user if they wish to log off after downloads.

   Downloading then commences, if the user selected log off after downloads
then if the downloads were successful it will display a count down from
10 to 0 and then kicks the user off, otherwise it will display a transfer
statistics screen. That's all it does!
   
@ENDNODE


